    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm able to reproduce this. The reason for this bug is that we receive `contact-request` message which triggers `:contact-request-received` event that dispatches `update-contact!` event.\r\n\r\nQuickfix would be comparing contact `last-updated` and message timestamp and do not run update if message is older. But this looks more like workaround so i have more general question - why do we process `contact-request` event for contact that already added? https://github.com/status-im/status-react/blob/develop/src/status_im/protocol/handlers.cljs#L495",
